### BLOCK 2 — Complete Workout Flow

2.1 Start a Push A workout
    ACTION: tap Train tab → tap Push chip → tap Push A card → tap Start
    EXPECT: session state = TRAINING
    EXPECT: Dynamic Island shows: dot (green pulse) · 00:00 · 0/4
    EXPECT: island collapsed by default, expands on tap

2.2 Log 4 sets on Bench Press
    ACTION: enter kg=90, reps=8, rpe=8 → tap Finish Set × 4
    EXPECT: set rows progress: Locked → Active → Done/PR
    EXPECT: set counter in island: 1/4 → 2/4 → 3/4 → 4/4
    EXPECT: 4/4 counter color = #00c86e (green)
    EXPECT: rest timer auto-starts after each set (active state, green ring)
    EXPECT: after 4/4 — auto-advance to next exercise after 600ms

2.3 Complete full session (Training → Core → Stretch → Summary)
    ACTION: complete all exercises → session auto-advances to Core
    EXPECT: session state transitions: TRAINING → CORE → STRETCH → SUMMARY
    EXPECT: progress line in island: ~75% at CORE start, ~90% at STRETCH, 100% at SUMMARY
    EXPECT: Core selected = least-used of A/B/C (check core_usage in IndexedDB)

2.4 Save workout
    ACTION: tap Save in Summary modal
    EXPECT: workout written to IndexedDB `workouts` store
    EXPECT: record added to `sync_queue` store
    EXPECT: sync_queue item format: { id, action: 'UPSERT', table: 'workouts', payload, created_at }
    EXPECT: sync status dot in Profile changes to 'syncing' then 'synced'
    EXPECT: NO data written to Supabase before Save is tapped

2.5 Verify Supabase received the workout
    EXPECT: row present in Supabase workouts table with correct device_id
    EXPECT: sets column is valid JSONB array
    EXPECT: updated_at auto-set by trigger
    EXPECT: sync_queue cleared after successful HTTP 200

